title: Another scam YouTube livestream running, lots of $ stolen
text:
Saw this on YouTube, another streaming scam . Just putting this out there.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gduoM8PWnEA

8 streams running with 5k fake viewers each: https://www.youtube.com/@tesla_23_us_/streams

(the channel is obviously hacked and repurposed to run this scam)

domain: www . muskway . net (scam website)

lots of crypto

https://blockchair.com/bitcoin/address/15Dn3Jaf9NmFZVMiZfr8WWnFFXqRDdAv22

https://blockchair.com/dogecoin/address/DBFKBvy8SPXi4ie5yT4RamJLkyjJfoqQNA

What does YouTube stand to gain by not doing anything about it? I wonder if there is some scheme where YouTube employees are paid off to allow it to run or if it's good for engagement. The only explanation has to be negligence or even malice given that the scams are so obvious and it has been bought to youtube's attention now for something like 3 years even as far back as 2019.

This has to be the best scam ever. No one getting in trouble for this, unlike the NFT frauds. It flies under the radar, unlike NFT rug pulls which get much more attention but make less money and less consistent.

title: ChatGPT: How many letters has the string “djsjcnnrjfkalcr”?
text:
Do you have a simple example that ChatGPT is not an AGI? I mean - the examples that are so simple that anyone could do and ChatGPT shows a total lack of understanding of the simple underlying concepts?

Here is my example:

Q: How many letters has the string "djsjcnnrjfkalcr"?

A: The string "djsjcnnrjfkalcr" has 16 letters. Is there anything else I can help with?

Q: Are you sure?

A: Yes, I am sure. The string "djsjcnnrjfkalcr" has 16 letters. If you count the number of individual characters in the string, you will see that it has 16 letters. Is there anything else I can help with?

Q: Can you split it in half into two strings then?

A: Sure! Here is how you can split the string "djsjcnnrjfkalcr" in half:

string1 = "djsjcnnr" string2 = "jfkalcr"

Each of these two strings has 8 letters. Is there anything else I can help with?
